llim\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"_blank\\\",\\\"rel\\\":\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"transition-colors hover:text-clay\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"X\\\"}]]}]]}]}]]}]]}]]}]],null],null],\\\"couldBeIntercepted\\\":false,\\\"initialHead\\\":[null,\\\"$Ld\\\"],\\\"globalErrorComponent\\\":\\\"$e\\\",\\\"missingSlots\\\":\\\"$Wf\\\"}]\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"10:I[2972,[\\\"972\\\",\\\"static/chunks/972-0fea25be27918f94.js\\\",\\\"308\\\",\\\"static/chunks/app/blog/%5Bslug%5D/page-509dcbc32cb4be24.js\\\"],\\\"\\\"]\\n11:T1427,\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"\\u003cp\\u003eIn this post, we're going to explore OpenAI's new \\u003cstrong\\u003eAdvanced Voice Mode (AVM)\\u003c/strong\\u003e, focusing on its capabilities, limitations, and how it performs in \\u003cstrong\\u003eSomali language\\u003c/strong\\u003e based on our tests. I teamed up with \\u003cstrong\\u003eMuhammad\\u003c/strong\\u003e (\\u003ca href=\\\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/muhaksim/\\\"\\u003e@muhaksim\\u003c/a\\u003e) to put this new mode through its paces, and we came away with some interesting findings!\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003chr\\u003e\\n\\u003ch2\\u003eWhat is OpenAI's Advanced Voice Mode?\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eOpenAI's Advanced Voice Mode is a newly launched feature in ChatGPT designed to enhance the conversational experience through more natural and interactive voice communication. It's part of the latest innovations in natural language processing, designed to recognize and produce speech across multiple languages.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eKey Aspects of AVM:\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\n\\u003cul\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eLaunch and Availability\\u003c/strong\\u003e: Rolled out to ChatGPT Plus and Teams subscribers on September 24, 2024. Plans to extend to Enterprise and Edu customers soon, but currently unavailable in several regions, including the EU and UK.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eNew Interface\\u003c/strong\\u003e: Features a blue animated sphere instead of the previous black dots, making interactions more engaging.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eVoice Options\\u003c/strong\\u003e: Introduces five new voices (Arbor, Maple, Sol, Spruce, and Vale), bringing the total to nine.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eTechnology\\u003c/strong\\u003e: Built on GPT-4's audio capabilities, allowing for real-time conversations that can pick up on non-verbal cues.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003c/ul\\u003e\\n\\u003chr\\u003e\\n\\u003ch2\\u003eKey Features of AVM\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\n\\u003col\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eNatural Conversations\\u003c/strong\\u003e: Capable of understanding speech speed and emotional tone, creating more dynamic interactions.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eMultilingual support\\u003c/strong\\u003e: Effortlessly switches between languages like English and Somali.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eReal-time adaptation\\u003c/strong\\u003e: Learns on the fly, adjusting pronunciations and improving based on feedback.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eCustomization\\u003c/strong\\u003e: Allows personalization through Custom Instructions and Memory features (though not fully integrated yet).\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eInteractive learning\\u003c/strong\\u003e: Adapts to specific pronunciations and learning patterns.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003c/ol\\u003e\\n\\u003cblockquote\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eScreenshot 1\\u003c/strong\\u003e: \\u003cimg src=\\\"/imgs/multi.jpeg\\\" alt=\\\"Multilingual Switching\\\"\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003c/blockquote\\u003e\\n\\u003chr\\u003e\\n\\u003ch2\\u003eOur Test: Performance in Somali\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\n\\u003ch3\\u003e🌟 \\u003cstrong\\u003eWhat We Liked\\u003c/strong\\u003e\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\n\\u003col\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eEffortless Language Switching\\u003c/strong\\u003e: Smooth transitions between Somali and English.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eLearning Capability\\u003c/strong\\u003e: Quickly adapted to pronunciation corrections, like the Somali letter \\\"C.\\\"\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eText Generation\\u003c/strong\\u003e: Excellent GPT-4-powered text generation in Somali, with high fluency and coherence.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003c/ol\\u003e\\n\\u003cblockquote\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eScreenshot 2\\u003c/strong\\u003e: \\u003cimg src=\\\"/imgs/story.jpeg\\\" alt=\\\"Somali Text Generation\\\"\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003c/blockquote\\u003e\\n\\u003ch3\\u003e🚩 \\u003cstrong\\u003eAreas for Improvement\\u003c/strong\\u003e\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\n\\u003col\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eTranscription Accuracy\\u003c/strong\\u003e: Inconsistent at times, especially with random characters or words.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003ePronunciation Challenges\\u003c/strong\\u003e:\\n\\u003cul\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eMispronunciation of Somali letters like \\\"X\\\" and \\\"C.\\\"\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003c/ul\\u003e\\n\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003c/ol\\u003e\\n\\u003chr\\u003e\\n\\u003ch2\\u003eImprovements We Hope to See\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\n\\u003cul\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eEnhanced Transcription\\u003c/strong\\u003e: Especially for non-Western languages like Somali.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eBetter Handling of Complex Phonetics\\u003c/strong\\u003e: Improved pronunciation of language-specific sounds.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003ePersistent Learning\\u003c/strong\\u003e: Ability to retain learned pronunciations across multiple sessions.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003c/ul\\u003e\\n\\u003chr\\u003e\\n\\u003ch2\\u003eTechnical Insights and Limitations\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\n\\u003cul\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eUsage Limits\\u003c/strong\\u003e: Subscribers may face restrictions on daily voice interaction time.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eRegional Availability\\u003c/strong\\u003e: Not yet available in all regions, notably absent in the EU and UK.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eOngoing Improvements\\u003c/strong\\u003e: OpenAI claims enhancements in accent understanding and conversation fluidity since alpha testing.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003c/ul\\u003e\\n\\u003chr\\u003e\\n\\u003ch2\\u003eFinal Thoughts\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eThe Advanced Voice Mode represents a significant leap in making AI interactions more intuitive and engaging. While there are still challenges, particularly with languages like Somali, the progress is exciting. Future iterations will likely address current limitations, making it even more robust for diverse language applications.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cblockquote\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eScreenshot 3\\u003c/strong\\u003e: \\u003cimg src=\\\"/imgs/teach.jpeg\\\" alt=\\\"Learning Pronunciations\\\"\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003c/blockquote\\u003e\\n\\u003chr\\u003e\\n\\u003ch2\\u003eSpecial Thanks\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eA special thanks to \\u003cstrong\\u003eMuhammed Khasim\\u003c/strong\\u003e for his invaluable insights and feedback during our testing of OpenAI's Advanced Voice Mode.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003ch2\\u003eWatch Our Test on YouTube\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eWe recorded our test of AVM in action. Check out the full video here:\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003ca href=\\\"https://youtu.be/cmzi7sdWzSc\\\"\\u003e\\u003cimg src=\\\"/imgs/yt.png\\\" alt=\\\"Watch on YouTube\\\"\\u003e\\u003c/a\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003chr\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eRemember, while AVM feels almost human-like in its interactions, it's important to note that it doesn't possess genuine emotions or consciousness. It's a sophisticated algorithm designed to interpret and respond to user inputs in a natural, conversational manner.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"7:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"main\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6 px-4 pb-8 pt-10 sm:px-6\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L10\\\",null,{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/blog\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"inline-block font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink/50 transition-colors hover:text-clay\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"← Back to writing\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink/40\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"2024-09-28\\\",\\\" · \\\",\\\"7 min read\\\"]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h1\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-1 text-2xl leading-tight sm:text-3xl\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"OpenAI's Advanced Voice Mode: A Deep Dive and Somali Language Test\\\"}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"article\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"prose max-w-none prose-headings:text-ink prose-p:text-ink/80 prose-a:text-clay prose-strong:text-ink prose-code:text-clay prose-code:before:content-none prose-code:after:content-none\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"$11\\\"}}]]}]\\nd:[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"meta\\\",\\\"0\\\",{\\\"name\\\":\\\"viewport\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"meta\\\",\\\"1\\\",{\\\"charSet\\\":\\\"utf-8\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"title\\\",\\\"2\\\",{\\\"children\\\":\\\"Abdihamid Moallim\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"meta\\\",\\\"3\\\",{\\\"name\\\":\\\"description\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Software engineer. Building web apps, internal tools, and AI-backed products.\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"link\\\",\\\"4\\\",{\\\"rel\\\":\\\"icon\\\",\\\"href\\\":\\\"/favicon.ico\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"image/x-icon\\\",\\\"sizes\\\":\\\"150x150\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"link\\\",\\\"5\\\",{\\\"rel\\\":\\\"icon\\\",\\\"href\\\":\\\"/icon.png?02db24294edd3330\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"image/png\\\",\\\"sizes\\\":\\\"150x150\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"meta\\\",\\\"6\\\",{\\\"name\\\":\\\"next-size-adjust\\\"}]]\\n6:null\\n\"])</script></body></html>","rsc":"3:I[4707,[],\"\"]\n5:I[6423,[],\"\"]\n6:I[8003,[\"310\",\"static/chunks/0e5ce63c-87c8b437464bdc9c.js\",\"972\",\"static/chunks/972-0fea25be27918f94.js\",\"566\",\"static/chunks/566-a97c572560d10c0d.js\",\"185\",\"static/chunks/app/layout-04e2ba14e7dea6d8.js\"],\"\"]\n7:I[432,[\"310\",\"static/chunks/0e5ce63c-87c8b437464bdc9c.js\",\"972\",\"static/chunks/972-0fea25be27918f94.js\",\"566\",\"static/chunks/566-a97c572560d10c0d.js\",\"185\",\"static/chunks/app/layout-04e2ba14e7dea6d8.js\"],\"default\"]\n4:[\"slug\",\"openai-advanced-voice-model-deep-dive\",\"d\"]\n0:[\"hiXGNe6nL8Cs5T5pPWCFv\",[[[\"\",{\"children\":[\"blog\",{\"children\":[[\"slug\",\"openai-advanced-voice-model-deep-dive\",\"d\"],{\"children\":[\"__PAGE__?{\\\"slug\\\":\\\"openai-advanced-voice-model-deep-dive\\\"}\",{}]}]}]},\"$undefined\",\"$undefined\",true],[\"\",{\"children\":[\"blog\",{\"children\":[[\"slug\",\"openai-advanced-voice-model-deep-dive\",\"d\"],{\"children\":[\"__PAGE__\",{},[[\"$L1\",\"$L2\",null],null],null]},[null,[\"$\",\"$L3\",null,{\"parallelRouterKey\":\"children\",\"segmentPath\":[\"children\",\"blog\",\"children\",\"$4\",\"children\"],\"error\":\"$undefined\",\"errorStyles\":\"$undefined\",\"errorScripts\":\"$undefined\",\"template\":[\"$\",\"$L5\",null,{}],\"templateStyles\":\"$undefined\",\"templateScripts\":\"$undefined\",\"notFound\":\"$undefined\",\"notFoundStyles\":\"$undefined\"}]],null]},[null,[\"$\",\"$L3\",null,{\"parallelRouterKey\":\"children\",\"segmentPath\":[\"children\",\"blog\",\"children\"],\"error\":\"$undefined\",\"errorStyles\":\"$undefined\",\"errorScripts\":\"$undefined\",\"template\":[\"$\",\"$L5\",null,{}],\"templateStyles\":\"$undefined\",\"templateScripts\":\"$undefined\",\"notFound\":\"$undefined\",\"notFoundStyles\":\"$undefined\"}]],null]},[[[[\"$\",\"link\",\"0\",{\"rel\":\"stylesheet\",\"href\":\"/_next/static/css/f7c0bb5f82096374.css\",\"precedence\":\"next\",\"crossOrigin\":\"$undefined\"}]],[\"$\",\"html\",null,{\"lang\":\"en\",\"className\":\"__variable_f367f3 __variable_3c557b __variable_814fbd\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"head\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L6\",null,{\"async\":true,\"src\":\"https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=G-ZBHQKS3HR1\"}],[\"$\",\"$L6\",null,{\"id\":\"google-analytics\",\"strategy\":\"afterInteractive\",\"children\":\"\\n            window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];\\n            function gtag(){dataLayer.push(arguments);}\\n            gtag('js', new Date());\\n            gtag('config', 'G-ZBHQKS3HR1');\\n          \"}]]}],[\"$\",\"body\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L7\",null,{}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"pt-14\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L3\",null,{\"parallelRouterKey\":\"children\",\"segmentPath\":[\"children\"],\"error\":\"$undefined\",\"errorStyles\":\"$undefined\",\"errorScripts\":\"$undefined\",\"template\":[\"$\",\"$L5\",null,{}],\"templateStyles\":\"$undefined\",\"templateScripts\":\"$undefined\",\"notFound\":[[\"$\",\"title\",null,{\"children\":\"404: This page could not be found.\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"style\":{\"fontFamily\":\"system-ui,\\\"Segoe UI\\\",Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,\\\"Apple Color Emoji\\\",\\\"Segoe UI Emoji\\\"\",\"height\":\"100vh\",\"textAlign\":\"center\",\"display\":\"flex\",\"flexDirection\":\"column\",\"alignItems\":\"center\",\"justifyContent\":\"center\"},\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"style\",null,{\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"body{color:#000;background:#fff;margin:0}.next-error-h1{border-right:1px solid rgba(0,0,0,.3)}@media (prefers-color-scheme:dark){body{color:#fff;background:#000}.next-error-h1{border-right:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.3)}}\"}}],[\"$\",\"h1\",null,{\"className\":\"next-error-h1\",\"style\":{\"display\":\"inline-block\",\"margin\":\"0 20px 0 0\",\"padding\":\"0 23px 0 0\",\"fontSize\":24,\"fontWeight\":500,\"verticalAlign\":\"top\",\"lineHeight\":\"49px\"},\"children\":\"404\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"style\":{\"display\":\"inline-block\"},\"children\":[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"style\":{\"fontSize\":14,\"fontWeight\":400,\"lineHeight\":\"49px\",\"margin\":0},\"children\":\"This page could not be found.\"}]}]]}]}]],\"notFoundStyles\":[]}],[\"$\",\"footer\",null,{\"className\":\"border-t border-ink/10 py-6\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mx-auto flex max-w-6xl flex-col items-center justify-between gap-3 px-4 text-sm text-ink/50 sm:flex-row sm:px-6\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"children\":[\"© \",2026,\" Abdihamid Moallim\"]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"a\",\"LinkedIn\",{\"href\":\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/abmoallim/\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"transition-colors hover:text-clay\",\"children\":\"LinkedIn\"}],[\"$\",\"a\",\"GitHub\",{\"href\":\"https://github.com/abmoallim\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"transition-colors hover:text-clay\",\"children\":\"GitHub\"}],[\"$\",\"a\",\"X\",{\"href\":\"https://x.com/abmoallim\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"transition-colors hover:text-clay\",\"children\":\"X\"}]]}]]}]}]]}]]}]]}]],null],null],[\"$L8\",null]]]]\n9:I[2972,[\"972\",\"static/chunks/972-0fea25be27918f94.js\",\"308\",\"static/chunks/app/blog/%5Bslug%5D/page-509dcbc32cb4be24.js\"],\"\"]\na:T1427,<p>In this post, we're going to explore OpenAI's new <strong>Advanced Voice Mode (AVM)</strong>, focusing on its capabilities, limitations, and how it performs in <strong>Somali language</strong> based on our tests. I teamed up with <strong>Muhammad</strong> (<a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/muhaksim/\">@muhaksim</a>) to put this new mode through its paces, and we came away with some interesting findings!</p>\n<hr>\n<h2>What is OpenAI's Advanced Voice Mode?</h2>\n<p>OpenAI's Advanced Voice Mode is a newly launched feature in ChatGPT designed to enhance the conversational experience through more natural and interactive voice communication. It's part of the latest innovations in natural language processing, designed to recognize and produce speech across multiple languages.</p>\n<h3>Key Aspects of AVM:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Launch and Availability</strong>: Rolled out to ChatGPT Plus and Teams subscribers on September 24, 2024. Plans to extend to Enterprise and Edu customers soon, but currently unavailable in several regions, including the EU and UK.</li>\n<li><strong>New Interface</strong>: Features a blue animated sphere instead of the previous black dots, making interactions more engaging.</li>\n<li><strong>Voice Options</strong>: Introduces five new voices (Arbor, Maple, Sol, Spruce, and Vale), bringing the total to nine.</li>\n<li><strong>Technology</strong>: Built on GPT-4's audio capabilities, allowing for real-time conversations that can pick up on non-verbal cues.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h2>Key Features of AVM</h2>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Natural Conversations</strong>: Capable of understanding speech speed and emotional tone, creating more dynamic interactions.</li>\n<li><strong>Multilingual support</strong>: Effortlessly switches between languages like English and Somali.</li>\n<li><strong>Real-time adaptation</strong>: Learns on the fly, adjusting pronunciations and improving based on feedback.</li>\n<li><strong>Customization</strong>: Allows personalization through Custom Instructions and Memory features (though not fully integrated yet).</li>\n<li><strong>Interactive learning</strong>: Adapts to specific pronunciations and learning patterns.</li>\n</ol>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Screenshot 1</strong>: <img src=\"/imgs/multi.jpeg\" alt=\"Multilingual Switching\"></p>\n</blockquote>\n<hr>\n<h2>Our Test: Performance in Somali</h2>\n<h3>🌟 <strong>What We Liked</strong></h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Effortless Language Switching</strong>: Smooth transitions between Somali and English.</li>\n<li><strong>Learning Capability</strong>: Quickly adapted to pronunciation corrections, like the Somali letter \"C.\"</li>\n<li><strong>Text Generation</strong>: Excellent GPT-4-powered text generation in Somali, with high fluency and coherence.</li>\n</ol>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Screenshot 2</strong>: <img src=\"/imgs/story.jpeg\" alt=\"Somali Text Generation\"></p>\n</blockquote>\n<h3>🚩 <strong>Areas for Improvement</strong></h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Transcription Accuracy</strong>: Inconsistent at times, especially with random characters or words.</li>\n<li><strong>Pronunciation Challenges</strong>:\n<ul>\n<li>Mispronunciation of Somali letters like \"X\" and \"C.\"</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<hr>\n<h2>Improvements We Hope to See</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Enhanced Transcription</strong>: Especially for non-Western languages like Somali.</li>\n<li><strong>Better Handling of Complex Phonetics</strong>: Improved pronunciation of language-specific sounds.</li>\n<li><strong>Persistent Learning</strong>: Ability to retain learned pronunciations across multiple sessions.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h2>Technical Insights and Limitations</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Usage Limits</strong>: Subscribers may face restrictions on daily voice interaction time.</li>\n<li><strong>Regional Availability</strong>: Not yet available in all regions, notably absent in the EU and UK.</li>\n<li><strong>Ongoing Improvements</strong>: OpenAI claims enhancements in accent understanding and conversation fluidity since alpha testing.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h2>Final Thoughts</h2>\n<p>The Advanced Voice Mode represents a significant leap in making AI interactions more intuitive and engaging. While there are still challenges, particularly with languages like Somali, the progress is exciting. Future iterations will likely address current limitations, making it even more robust for diverse language applications.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Screenshot 3</strong>: <img src=\"/imgs/teach.jpeg\" alt=\"Learning Pronunciations\"></p>\n</blockquote>\n<hr>\n<h2>Special Thanks</h2>\n<p>A special thanks to <strong>Muhammed Khasim</strong> for his invaluable insights and feedback during our testing of OpenAI's Advanced Voice Mode.</p>\n<h2>Watch Our Test on YouTube</h2>\n<p>We recorded our test of AVM in action. Check out the full video here:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://youtu.be/cmzi7sdWzSc\"><img src=\"/imgs/yt.png\" alt=\"Watch on YouTube\"></a></p>\n<hr>\n<p>Remember, while AVM feels almost human-like in its interactions, it's important to note that it doesn't possess genuine emotions or consciousness. It's a sophisticated algorithm designed to interpret and respond to user inputs in a natural, conversational manner.</p>\n2:[\"$\",\"main\",null,{\"className\":\"mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6 px-4 pb-8 pt-10 sm:px-6\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L9\",null,{\"href\":\"/blog\",\"className\":\"inline-block font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink/50 transition-colors hover:text-clay\",\"children\":\"← Back to writing\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink/40\",\"children\":[\"2024-09-28\",\" · \",\"7 min read\"]}],[\"$\",\"h1\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-1 text-2xl leading-tight sm:text-3xl\",\"children\":\"OpenAI's Advanced Voice Mode: A Deep Dive and Somali Language Test\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"article\",null,{\"className\":\"prose max-w-none prose-headings:text-ink prose-p:text-ink/80 prose-a:text-clay prose-strong:text-ink prose-code:text-clay prose-code:before:content-none prose-code:after:content-none\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$a\"}}]]}]\n8:[[\"$\",\"meta\",\"0\",{\"name\":\"viewport\",\"content\":\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"1\",{\"charSet\":\"utf-8\"}],[\"$\",\"title\",\"2\",{\"children\":\"Abdihamid Moallim\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"3\",{\"name\":\"description\",\"content\":\"Software engineer. Building web apps, internal tools, and AI-backed products.\"}],[\"$\",\"link\",\"4\",{\"rel\":\"icon\",\"href\":\"/favicon.ico\",\"type\":\"image/x-icon\",\"sizes\":\"150x150\"}],[\"$\",\"link\",\"5\",{\"rel\":\"icon\",\"href\":\"/icon.png?02db24294edd3330\",\"type\":\"image/png\",\"sizes\":\"150x150\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"6\",{\"name\":\"next-size-adjust\"}]]\n1:null\n"}